      <h1 class='title'>Regulatory Impact Assessment (Compliance)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 03 April 2003 vol 402 c70WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_70ws' title='Col. 70WS &mdash; HC Deb 03 April 2003 vol 402 c70WS' name='column_70ws' href='#column_70ws' rel='bookmark'>70WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0402P0-05262'>
        <a name='S6CV0402P0_20030403_CWS_10'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-douglas-alexander' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0402P0_20030403_CWS_10' title='Link to this speech by Mr Douglas Alexander' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-douglas-alexander" title="Mr Douglas Alexander">The Minister of State, Cabinet Office (Mr. Douglas Alexander)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0402P0-05262">A baseline for measuring the level of compliance with the Regulatory Impact Assessment is today being placed on the website of the Cabinet Office Regulatory Impact Unit<span class="underline">http://www.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/regulation.</span> An exercise in December 2002 to establish a snapshot of the level of compliance provided a figure of 92 per cent. We will keep this under six monthly review and strive not only to maintain this level of compliance but improve it. In addition, we recognise the need to increase the quality of RIAs and the value they add to the policy making process. We are working closely with departments to identify ways of achieving this.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
